&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for a highly motivated and enthusiastic individual to join the Dermatology Administration Team as a Support Typist.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To be successful you will have demonstrably competent audio-typing skills, organisational and communication skills. You must have a flexible and professional approach to the work and enjoy the variety of communicating with a wide range of people both internal and external to the Royal Cornwall Hospitals NHS Trust. This includes providing cover for colleagues as necessary. This is a busy role and the post holder will need to be able to use their own initiative.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This is a part time, fixed term post for a period of 12 months to cover maternity leave working 30 hours per week.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Proposed Interview Date: Week beginning Monday 16th November 2020.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sarah Lague - Clinical Admin Lead on Tel: 01872252353. Or email: sarah.lague@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
